                <head>100. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>At the 443d meeting of the National Security Council on May 5, 1960, the Council
                    heard and discussed presentations by Drs. <persName corresp="#p_YDHF1"
                        >York</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_SHE1">Scoville</persName> on the
                    history of U.S. and Soviet long-range missile development. (Memorandum of
                    discussion by <persName corresp="#p_BMW2">Boggs</persName>; <persName
                        corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> Library, <persName corresp="#p_WAC1"
                        >Whitman</persName> File, <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Records) See
                    the Supplement.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
